who says goodbye or they do.

194
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:17,000
But it's- it's the
goodbye that comes

195
00:11:17,066 --> 00:11:18,866
from the one you
love the most...

196
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:21,433
that's the one that ends
up hurting you the most.

197
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:26,166
Well, you see,
I used to work at Tirol.

198
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:29,633
Mr. Ueda is a very nice person.

199
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:31,966
When he wasn't busy,
he'd even teach me

200
00:11:32,033 --> 00:11:35,133
how to bake cakes
and cookies and things.

201
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:38,766
It's amazing what a sweet

202
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:41,700
and wonderful guy he can be.

203
00:11:41,766 --> 00:11:46,233
He blushes easily,
and he's really cute too.

204
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,766
And so...

205
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:51,433
Well, I fell in love.

206
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:54,666
And one day, I summoned
up all my courage,

207
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:56,100
and asked him out.

208
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,633
I love you.

209
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:07,266
Uh, I uh, love you, too.

210
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,833
R-Really?

211
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:10,600
Y-Yes.

212
00:12:10,666 --> 00:12:12,000
Really for real?

213
00:12:12,066 --> 00:12:13,866
R-Really, for real.

214
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,566
I had that outfit made
just for you, Yumi.

215
00:12:21,166 --> 00:12:22,200
Well, I thought it would be nice

216
00:12:22,266 --> 00:12:24,066
if you could keep working here,

217
00:12:24,133 --> 00:12:29,066
but, do you think
this is a good idea?

218
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:31,866
I mean, I'm a lot older
than you are, Yumi.

219
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:36,200
