266
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:22,866
I'm sure that must have
sounded very strange!

267
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,566
Playing back the second file.

268
00:14:25,633 --> 00:14:28,233
Now that your marriage,

269
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,966
to a Persocom, has ended so
abruptly in a traffic accident,

270
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,633
how does that make you feel?

271
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:33,933
Is it true that the Persocom

272
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,533
protected you in the accident?

273
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,466
Would you ever consider
marrying another Persocom?

274
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:40,166
Do you plan to
cremate the Persocom?

275
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:42,400
Or are you just
gonna throw it out?

276
00:14:42,466 --> 00:14:44,566
Mr. Ueda, apparently,
the Persocom

277
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:46,800
actually saved your
life, is that right?

278
00:14:46,866 --> 00:14:48,300
She's not just a Persocom.

279
00:14:48,366 --> 00:14:51,066
Please don't generalize and
diminish her life like that.

280
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,866
My wife had a proper name.

281
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:56,433
If you don't mind,
her name was "Yumi."

282
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,966
Huh?

283
00:14:59,466 --> 00:15:00,666
Yumi?

284
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,200
I knew when I saw this,

285
00:15:02,266 --> 00:15:06,433
that I would never be
able to measure up to her!

286
00:15:10,066 --> 00:15:11,233
Yumi.

287
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,733
Yumi looked hurt too.

288
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:18,166
She had lots of water
coming from her eyes.

289
00:15:18,233 --> 00:15:21,033
Water? You mean tears.

290
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,900
Why do tears fall out?

291
00:15:23,966 --> 00:15:27,033
Tears flow from happy times
and from sad times.

292
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:30,633
So Yumi's tears were flowing
out because she is happy?

293
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:33,366
No, I'm sure those were
because she was sad.

294
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:34,633
She said that it
just made her sad

295
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,733
whenever I was around her.

296
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,466
There's really no
other way to explain it:

297
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:40,000
she must hate me, that's all.

298
00:15:40,066 --> 00:15:41,266
What is hate?

299
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:44,266
It means that she doesn't
want to be together.

300
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:48,333
Why was Yumi out there,
looking inside the store?

301
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,833
She wants to be close
to someone she hates?

302
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:52,866
Well, not really...

303
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:56,000
Yumi is always looking
inside the store from outside.

304
00:15:56,066 --> 00:15:57,066
Huh?

305
00:15:57,133 --> 00:15:59,700
Over there; she was
always watching you,

306
00:15:59,766 --> 00:16:01,500
and her face looked painful.

307
00:16:01,566 --> 00:16:03,400
But she was different
a few minutes ago.

308
00:16:03,466 --> 00:16:05,866
When Chi put on this outfit,

309
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:09,200
lots of tears came
from Yumi's eyes.

310
00:16:09,266 --> 00:16:11,600
Right after she
saw these clothes.

311
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,533
That outfit is Yumi's.

312
00:16:13,866 --> 00:16:15,533
Why does Yumi look
like she feels hurt

313
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,800
when she sees
this outfit on Chi?

314
00:16:18,866 --> 00:16:22,133
Now Manager has a painful look.

315
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,733
Painful is very hard.

316
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,133
What would be best to do?

317
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:28,100
What does Manager want to do?

318
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:29,966
What do I want to do?

319
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:33,433
I guess I...

320
00:16:34,966 --> 00:16:38,966
Chi, I need to ask
you a favor of you.

321
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,066
So when it hit me like that,

322
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:43,433
that I'd be somehow
be compared to her...

323
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:46,033
the idea was just too awful.

324
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,300
Because, well
Persocoms always do

325
00:16:48,366 --> 00:16:50,333
everything so perfectly.

326
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,200
I thought it was
better to say goodbye

327
00:16:52,266 --> 00:16:54,600
before I disappointed him.

328
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:56,266
But it's just no good.

329
00:16:56,333 --> 00:17:00,233
It's even harder now than
it was before we broke up!

330
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:02,500
I understand.

331
00:17:07,966 --> 00:17:10,300
It was tough for you, wasn't it?

332
00:17:10,366 --> 00:17:13,933
Because by then you cared
about Mr. Ueda too much.

333
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,566
You're like a big brother.

334
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:20,433
So I'm like your big brother?

335
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:23,533
But anyway, I'm sure it was
just as tough on Mr. Ueda,

336
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,066
And even though his
first wife was a Persocom,

337
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:29,133
I'm sure it wasn't just
some decision he made lightly.

338
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:33,166
You're right. I know
that he wouldn't do that.

339
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,466
Yeah.

340
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:36,800
And if he was acting
that way towards you,

341
00:17:36,866 --> 00:17:38,100
it can only mean
that you must've been

342
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,266
very special to him, Yumi.

343
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,900
What happened to
her was terrible,

344
00:17:42,966 --> 00:17:44,300
and it must have been
the hardest time

345
00:17:44,366 --> 00:17:45,466
in his whole life.

346
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:46,900
And yet, in spite of everything,

347
00:17:46,966 --> 00:17:49,633
he was somehow able
to fall in love again.

348
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,900
I think that's just amazing.

349
00:17:51,966 --> 00:17:54,000
So the truth is, I don't think

350
00:17:54,066 --> 00:17:56,633
he'd ever compare you
with someone from his past.

351
00:17:57,966 --> 00:17:58,966
But what about you?

352
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:01,700
Wouldn't it bother you
just a teeny bit, Senpai?

353
00:18:01,766 --> 00:18:03,033
Me? Well,

354
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:08,533
I don't know.
Yeah, I guess I would.

355
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:11,666
But, I wouldn't make any
comparisons like that.

356
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,300
Why do you say that?

357
00:18:13,366 --> 00:18:15,300
Because I think
I can imagine how

358
00:18:15,366 --> 00:18:17,466
I'd feel if someone
did that to me.

359
00:18:18,766 --> 00:18:19,766
He couldn't do something

360
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,400
like that anymore than I could.

361
00:18:21,466 --> 00:18:23,133
He's not that type of person.

362
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:25,200
Thank you, Motosuwa.

363
00:18:25,266 --> 00:18:27,566
Chi!

364
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:28,766
Manager!

365
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:31,066
But how did you
know we were here?

366
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:33,733
Well, actually; I got
a little help from Chi.

367
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,500
She did me a really big favor;

368
00:18:35,566 --> 00:18:37,033
she was able to
locate Yumi by accessing

369
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,866
the number to
her mobile Persocom.

370
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:40,366
And here we are.

371
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:41,900
How could that be?

372
00:18:41,966 --> 00:18:44,000
I don't get it; it never rang.

373
00:18:44,066 --> 00:18:47,066
Huh?

374
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:49,933
I'm sorry to intrude
on you like this.

375
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,833
No, please come on in.

376
00:19:03,766 --> 00:19:05,333
I'm sorry, this is all my fault.

377
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,666
No, you didn't do
anything, Manager.

378
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:09,800
That's easy to say,
but it's not true.

379
00:19:09,866 --> 00:19:12,566
It is my fault; if I had
explained it to you properly,

380
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:14,933
I'd have spared you
every one of those tears.

381
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,700
The reason that
I decided to ask Yumi

382
00:19:18,766 --> 00:19:20,633
to get married to me
in the first place was

383
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,333
because of who she was.

384
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:25,400
It wasn't just because
she was a Persocom.

385
00:19:25,466 --> 00:19:26,566
And that's just how I felt

386
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:28,600
when I fell in
love with you, Yumi,

387
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,233
because of who you are.

388
00:19:32,033 --> 00:19:33,533
Yumi, somehow you think that

389
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:37,000
that "Yumi," the
Persocom, was perfect.

390
00:19:37,066 --> 00:19:40,466
But believe me;
it wasn't like that.

391
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:41,633
There are things
that they can do

392
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:43,000
because they're Persocoms,

393
00:19:43,066 --> 00:19:44,400
but there're some
things they can't do

394
00:19:44,466 --> 00:19:46,466
because they're Persocoms.

395
00:19:46,533 --> 00:19:49,066
It's really just
the same as people

396
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:53,200
having certain things they
can or can't do, that's all.

397
00:19:53,266 --> 00:19:57,966
I thought that I'd never
be able to fall in love again.

398
00:19:58,033 --> 00:20:00,233
Especially that I'd
never be able to fall

399
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,766
in love with another Persocom.

400
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,533
But, you know,

401
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,000
even if you were
a Persocom, Yumi,

402
00:20:07,066 --> 00:20:09,700
I think I would have fallen
in love with you anyway.

403
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:12,433
Oh, Yumi, I'm sorry!

404
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:14,533
What have I done?
I made you cry again!

405
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,233
Chi?

406
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,833
C-Chi?!

407
00:20:21,433 --> 00:20:22,933
Chi made a mistake.

408
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:27,233
Here. Manager said that
this outfit belongs to Yumi.

409
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,566
Thank you.

410
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:37,033
Manager, I, um, I'm sorry.

411
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:39,600
I'm really sorry.

412
00:20:39,666 --> 00:20:44,000
I was... I just...

413
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:48,600
Thank you for falling
in love with me!

414
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,233
Chi?

415
00:21:16,966 --> 00:21:18,000
There are things
that they can do

416
00:21:18,066 --> 00:21:19,500
because they're Persocoms,

417
00:21:19,566 --> 00:21:20,900
but there're some
things they can't do

418
00:21:20,966 --> 00:21:22,633
because they're Persocoms.

419
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:24,733
It's really just the
same as people having

420
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,200
certain things they can
or can't do, that's all.

421
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,666
Even if you were
a Persocom, Yumi,

422
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:34,866
I think I would have fallen
in love with you anyway.

423
00:21:38,233 --> 00:21:39,200
Chi.

424
00:21:39,266 --> 00:21:41,200
Hideki.

425
00:21:41,266 --> 00:21:43,566
Happy holding hands?

426
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:47,100
Chi...

427
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:02,933
Ah, it looks like The One
Just for Me has been decided.

428
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,933
I guess I have no choice
but to go over there now.

429
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:09,100
I hope that this turns
out to be a happy ending.

430
00:22:09,166 --> 00:22:10,433
Hm?

431
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,533
What's going on?

432
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,766
Nothing.

433
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:14,700
Hm?

434
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:03,200
One person completely
fills me up.

435
00:24:03,266 --> 00:24:06,100
I'm happy when
that person laughs.

436
00:24:06,166 --> 00:24:09,466
I'm happy when that
person is by my side.

437
00:24:09,533 --> 00:24:13,633
Yes. I feel happy when
that person is happy.

438
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:18,733
Different from the others,
that person is my dearest...

439
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,233
my special one...

440
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:23,666
"The One Just for Me."

441
